I am very sorry to write this, but I cannot recommend this game in absolutely any way but one: if you want to help the developer to make better games, then buy it ('cause everybody needs to eat, right?).

Minus:
The narrative is awful;
The art of the game is poor;
The SFX are cool in the first five puzzles, then just doesn't fit with the soundtrack;
The gameplay is quite defective: things don't go when you click-n-drag, and that's quite stressing;
The puzzles are way too easy. Even to relax.

Plus:
The music is alright;
The price is absolutely right.
(optional) If this is some sort of College work, or school project made it in a couple of weeks, then it seems quite good.

Conclusion:
The price (U$0,99) is fair, and you can buy it maybe for your 3-year-old kid, but don't expect a game better then 5/10.

